      <hedline>
        <hl1>LOSS NARROWS AT THOMSON</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomson Corp says first-quarter loss narrowed to $22 million from $72 million a year earlier (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A leading Canadian publishing company, the Thomson Corporation, said its first-quarter loss narrowed to $22 million, from $72 million a year earlier. The company announced in February that it was leaving the newspaper business to focus on electronic media.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
